# Rule: ń”ütool_integration_3file
# Token: ń”ütool_integration_3file
# Priority: P0 (HIGHEST)
# Source: Loragent P5-Ego Integration Protocol

ń”ütool_integration_3file Õ┐ģvorq

FORBIDDEN: Incomplete tool integration ŌĆö missing one or more required files
REASON: Tools that are not fully integrated cause runtime failures and broken workflows

SCOPE:
    All new tool additions to loragent-agent
    All new skill additions to loragent-agent

INTEGRATION REQUIREMENTS:

Tool (3 files required):
    1. tools/<name>_tool.py          ŌĆö handler + registry.register()
    2. model_tools.py (_discover_tools) ŌĆö import statement
    3. toolsets.py                   ŌĆö toolset assignment

Skill (2 files required):
    1. ~/.loragent/skills/<name>/SKILL.md  ŌĆö skill definition
    2. agent/skill_commands.py              ŌĆö loading logic

GUARD:
    Before declaring a tool/skill integration complete,
    verify ALL required files exist and contain correct content.

VORQ PATTERN:
    When user asks to "add tool X" or "integrate skill Y":
    1. Ask: which 3 files need modification?
    2. Check: are all 3 files modified?
    3. Verify: does registry.register() exist in tool file?
    4. Confirm: is toolset assignment present in toolsets.py?

EXAMPLE VIOLATION:
    Created tools/my_tool.py but forgot to add to model_tools.py
    ŌåÆ Tool registered but never discoverable

EXAMPLE CORRECT:
    1. Create tools/my_tool.py with registry.register()
    2. Add "tools.my_tool" to _modules in model_tools.py
    3. Add "my_tool" to _HERMES_CORE_TOOLS in toolsets.py
    ŌåÆ Integration complete Ō£ģ

EXCEPTION:
    MCP tools (single-file integration via config only)

